The param `fn` is passed a continuation handler that will cause this [Task](/_autogen/Classes/classbatt_1_1Task/) to wake up, causing `await` to return an instance of type `R` constructed from the arguments passed to the handler. For example, `await` can be used to turn an async socket read into a synchronous call:



```cpp
boost::asio::ip::tcp::socket s;

using ReadResult = std::pair<boost::system::error_code, std::size_t>;

ReadResult r = Task::await<ReadResult>([&](auto&& handler) {
    s.async_read_some(buffers, BATT_FORWARD(handler));
  });

if (r.first) {
  std::cout << "Error! ec=" << r.first;
} else {
  std::cout << r.second << " bytes were read.";
}
```
